"index_reference": "5172: offal",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The internal organs of an animal, traditionally regarded as being inferior to meat, and used as a symbol of disgrace.</p>\n<h2>Offal is symbolic of disgrace</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mal2:3\">MAL 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah3:6\">NAM 3:6</a></p>\n<h2>In animal sacrifices the offal was removed and burnt outside the camp</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:14\">EXO 29:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:11-Lev4:12\">LEV 4:11–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:17\">LEV 8:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:27\">LEV 16:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:3-Num19:5\">NUM 19:3–19:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:5\">NUM 19:5</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ bears the believer's disgrace</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb13:11-Heb13:13\">HEB 13:11–13:13</a></p>",
